<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-29-1014 </DOCNO><TEXT>An IBM AT computer interfaced to a small CAMAC system offers considerablepower without the complexity and expense of a large general-purpose system.The authors' system for time-resolved spectroscopy features menu-drivenFORTRAN-based software; high-resolution and high-speed 98K channels,5-{mu}s fixed dead time) ADCs; segmentable histogram memories (24-bitcounts) with large memory space for many histogram segments; independentlyvariable separate histogram dwell times; remote control via a CAMAC serialhighway; and ground isolation between the data acquisition equipmentand control computer by means of fiber optics.</TEXT></DOC>